<TITLE> BNP policy meet to discuss party shake-up </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, February 1 (bdnews24.com)The BNP national standing committee, its highest policy-making body, will meet Sunday evening to discuss the party's next steps after its huge defeat in the Dec 29 general election, said senior party members. "Khaleda Zia has already set in motion the task of party reorganisation, starting from the grassroots, which will go all the way up to the highest level," BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain told bdnews24.com "Khaleda will finalise some crucial decision making steps today (Sunday)," he said, referring to the standing committee meeting. BNP's office secretary Rizvi Ahmed told bdnews24.com: "Chaired by Khaleda Zia herself, this top decision making forum is expected to review the devastating defeat suffered by the party in the recently held JS polls." "The party's top decision makers will take important steps as regards reorganising the party afresh, which will be intimated to the mass media after the meeting." The party's standing committee members currently number 11:e M Saifur Rahman, Khandaker Delwar Hossain, Dr Khanadaker Mosharraf Hossain, Abdul Matin Chowdhury, Dr RA Ghani, Chowdhury Tanveer Ahmed Siddiqui, barrister Moudud Ahmed, advocate Khandaker Mahbubuddin, Lt Gen Mahbubur Rahman (retd) and M Shamsul Islam. They will meet at the chairperson's Gulshan office from around 7pm, said Rizvi. bdnews
